description.plain:
James Lee Baker (b. May 19, 1996), better known by his stage name BlocBoy JB, is a rapper from Memphis, Tennessee. He released six mixtapes from 2016-17, and his single “Shoot” and accompanying viral dance caught the attention of Drake. Drake connected with BlocBoy via producer Tay Keith, and they recorded the single “Look Alive.”

BlocBoy JB’s debut album SIMI, which is named for his slain friend, was released on May 4, 2018.

songs.full_title: Look Alive by BlocBoy JB (Ft. Drake)
songs.title: Look Alive

description.plain:
“Look Alive” is the first collaboration between Memphis rapper BlocBoy JB and Drake. Drake’s connection to Memphis can be attributed to his father Dennis, who is a Memphis native.

The song describes ties to Drake and BlocBoy JB’s crew in Tennessee. They get money and take care of each other, so people on the outside better “Look Alive” before they get taken down.

Compared to a very slow latter half of 2017 for Drake music, “Look Alive” follows his feature on Migos' “Walk It Talk It” and his two track EP Scary Hours for what is shaping up to be a busy 2018.

description.plain:
“Shoot” is a hard-hitting banger from Memphis rapper BlocBoy JB. The song appeared on three of BlocBoy’s projects: Who Am I 3, The Purple M&M as a bonus track, and SIMI.

The track is best known for being associated with the “shoot” dance, which became extremely popular and became more known after it was added into the video game Fortnite.

songs.full_title: Rover 2.0 by BlocBoy JB (Ft. 21 Savage)
songs.title: Rover 2.0

description.plain:
Hot on the heels of his Drake assisted smash-hit “Look Alive,” BlocBoy JB continues his run with a remix of his viral early 2018 hit “Rover,” this time with assistance from Atlanta’s own 21 Savage.

Rover 2.0 is from BlocBoys' tape, Simi, and sees him and 21 rapping about riding luxury cars like the songs' namesake, and keeping their rivals in check.

The two also filmed the official video together in Atlanta.
